 
<p>

Republicans made a deal to improve medical care for military veterans
who were poisoned by toxic substances while deployed.  Then they demanded
to change the deal, and ultimately <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2022/jul/28/republicans-bill-healthcare-military-veterans-jon-stewart">killed it</a>.
<p>
Military veterans used to be politically untouchable in the US, but in
2016 the wrecker started started <a href="https://stallman.org/archives/2017-sep-dec.html#20_October_2017_(White-supremacist_supporters)">showing public contempt</a> for veterans
and their families. Maybe that made them less sacrosanct.

 